P(A \cup B \cup C) = 1
P(B) = 2P(A) 
P(C) = 3P(A) 
P(A \cap B) = P(A \cap C) = P(B \cap C) 
P(A) \le \frac{1}{4} 
 1 = P(A \cup B \cup C) = 6P(A) - 3P(A \cap B) + P(A \cap B \cap C) 
\mathbb P(A)=a
\mathbb P(B)=2a
\mathbb P(C)=3a
\mathbb P(B\cap C)\geqslant \mathbb P(B)+\mathbb P(C)-1
\mathbb P(B\cap C)\geqslant5a-1
\mathbb P(A\cap B)=\mathbb P(B\cap C)
\mathbb P(A\cap B)\geqslant5a-1
\mathbb P(A\cap B)\leqslant \mathbb P(A)=a
a\geqslant5a-1
\mathbb P(A)=a\leqslant\frac14
x=P\big((A\cap B)\setminus C\big)
y=P(A\cap B\cap C)
a=P(A)-2x-y
b=P(B)-2x-y
c=P(C)-2x-y
A\setminus(B\cup C)
B\setminus(A\cup C)
C\setminus(A\cup B)
b=2a+2x+y
c=3a+4x+2y
b+2x+y=2(a+2x+y)=2a+4x+2y\;,
c+2x+y=3(a+2x+y)=3a+6x+3y\;,
\begin{align*} 1&=P(A\cup B\cup C)\\ &=a+b+c+3x+y\\ &=6a+9x+4y\\ &=4(a+2x+y)+2a+x\\ &=4P(A)+2a+x\;. \end{align*}
2a+x\ge 0
P(A)\le \frac{1}{4}
